<div class ="sectionHeading" id="concept_tags"><strong>Attach concept tag to an exercise</strong></div>
<p>Concept tags enable you to easily track and view all exercises linked to a concept. Attaching a concept tag to an exercise involves two processes, as described below:</p>
<p>
<em>Step 1: Create concept tag.</em>
  <ol>
    <li>From the Learning Plan, navigate to the Concepts page;</li>
    <p>
  		<%= image_tag("concept1.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "80%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
    <li>Click New Concept, enter concept name and click Create Concept.</li>
    <p>
  		<%= image_tag("concept2.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "80%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
  </ol>
<em>Step 2: Attach concept tag to an exercise.</em>
  <ol>
    <li>Return to the Topics section;</li>
    <li>Create a new exercise, or open an existing exercise;</li>
    <li>Select the concept tag from the dropdown Concept menu;</li>
    <br/>
  		<%= image_tag("concept3.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "80%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
    <li>Save exercise. Your exercise is now tagged.</li>
		<%= image_tag("concept4.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "80%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
</ol>
<p>You can view all exercises linked to a concept by navigating to the Concepts page and click on the concept name.</p>

